content:
Salesforce offers several tools to help you analyze your data and act on it. Reports and dashboards are built into Salesforce. Connect data and create interactive visualizations with CRM Analytics, a Salesforce-native tool. Tableau is a flexible analytics platform with cloud, on-premises, and desktop applications.

Reports and Dashboards

* Build a report
* Build a dashboard
* Export and connect reports to other tools
* Drill down into your reports to learn more
* Embed dashboards in Lightning Experience and the Home tab

CRM Analytics

* Connect to local Salesforce data
* Connect to remote data outside of Salesforce
* Clean, transform, and load data
* Explore and visualize your data
* Build CRM Analytics dashboards

Tableau

* Connect to Salesforce data
* Unlock hidden insights with Tableau for Data Cloud
* Structure data for analysis
* Get started with building views
* Analyze data

Reports and Dashboards also allow you to:

* Manage reports and dashboards on Analytics Home
* Improve report performance
* Control dashboard data visibility

CRM Analytics provides features such as:

* Creating and sharing CRM Analytics apps
* Deploying CRM Analytics industry apps and prebuilt apps
* Embedding dashboards everywhere
* Controlling access to the Analytics Studio

Tableau offers features such as:

* Publishing data sources and workbooks
* Scheduling extract refreshes
* Using parameters to make views more interactive
* Embedding Tableau views into Salesforce
title: Understanding Salesforce Analytics Tools
